projects.description:
Performing a ‘technical-institutional analysis of small dams in the Sana’a Basin, Yemen’
Activities performed:
-	Fieldwork including: qualitative assessment of community member’s involvement and position on groundwater abstraction around recharge dams; 
-	Consultations with federal ministries of agriculture and water resources; 
-	Presentations on research proposal writing and qualitative data analysis
-	Preparation and presentation of conference paper

Study into the Growth Corridor for the Tana and Beles Sub-basins: Endowments, Potential and Constraints, as part of a larger Tana-Beles Integrated Water Resources Development Project (TWIWRDP).
Activities performed:
-	Fieldwork including: inventory of landcover, climate, eta biomass analysis, agricultural potential and water resources availability assessment; 
-	Consultation with 15 woreda offices, regional bureaus of water and agriculture and the federal ministry of water resources; 
-	Workshop at MoWR on ‘Agricultural and irrigation potential assessment using remote sensing’.
